    "body": "NVIM v0.10.0-dev-1500+g3128cff6b-dirty\r\n\r\n\r\nFor example, the line underlined by ^ is all highlighted as a codeblock even though there is no closing backtick\r\n```\r\n'<  `<\t\t\tTo the first line or character of the last selected\r\n    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^  \r\n```\r\n\r\n## Screenshot of `motion.txt` with `set cole=0`\r\n![motion.txt](https://github.com/neovim/tree-sitter-vimdoc/assets/10135646/a566f0d1-3648-45d1-a0dc-a6ef927293ae)\r\n\r\n\r\nThe website repeats a character in this scenario\r\n```\r\n'<<\t\t\tTo the first line or character of the last selected\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Screenshot of Neovim online help\r\n![neovim-help](https://github.com/neovim/tree-sitter-vimdoc/assets/10135646/086a1c3a-4e8b-4324-9f23-6bb5b74dc973)\r\n\r\n\r\nSee ``:h `<``\r\nSee https://neovim.io/doc/user/motion.html#%60%3C\r\n\r\nIf you need any additional info please let me know ðŸ‘",
